[B] South Korea: 19 077 confirmed cases, 316 deaths (371 new cases -- 12 imported, 359 locally transmitted)
http://ncov.mohw.go.kr/en/bdBoardList.do?brdId=16&brdGubun=162&dataGubun=&ncvContSeq=&contSeq=&board_i=

[The 15th consecutive day with more than 100 newly confirmed cases. Notices 523 and 524 -- the latest analyses of the ongoing outbreak at https://www.cdc.go.kr/board.es?mid=a30402000000&bid=0030 -- provide details on clusters as of 0000 hours 28 Aug 2020. These involve multiple clusters, some faith-based, some school-based, and other areas of work or communal gatherings. Faith-based congregations are the predominant groups with cases although a hair salon and indoor fitness center have also been associated with clusters. Of the locally transmitted cases, 145 are in Seoul, 112 are in neighboring Gyeonggi province, and 27 are in Incheon. All 17 provinces have reported locally transmitted cases. Level 2 restrictions are being implemented, with no indoor dining and no in-person church services. - Mod.MPP]

[C] Italy: 263 949 total cases, 35 463 deaths [comparative 7-day averages have gone up by 101.7% from the preceding 7 days]
https://www.albengacorsara.it/doc/dpc-covid19-ita-scheda-regioni-2020-08-27.pdf

[The 7-day average comparison continues to show a marked increase in confirmed cases consistent with increasing transmission of the virus. - Mod.MPP]

[D] Iran: 367 796 total cases, 21 137 deaths
https://ifpnews.com/daily-covid-19-deaths-continue-to-decrease-in-iran

[E] USA: 6 046 634 total cases, 184 796 deaths [comparative 7-day averages have gone down by 9.1% for daily case count and reported mortality has gone up by 5.2% for reported deaths]
https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/usa-pdf/AUG27USDATASET_1598584399.pdf accessed at 22:10 EDT (GMT-4) and https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/usa-pdf/AUG27US7_1598584917.pdf

[With the greater availability of antigen testing for quick results, many states are not counting those individuals as confirmed cases. A map showing the testing rate per 100 000 population by state can be seen at https://covid.cdc.gov/covid-data-tracker/#testing. - Mod.MPP]

[F] Spain: 429 507 cases, 28 996 deaths [14-day population-based rate: 183.37/100 000 -- up from 7.74 on 25 Jun 2020 and up from 173.94 on 26 Aug 2020]
https://www.mscbs.gob.es/profesionales/saludPublica/ccayes/alertasActual/nCov/documentos/Actualizacion_194_COVID-19.pdf

[The 14-day average population-based rates reported by the Ministry remain high, consistent with the increasing daily newly confirmed cases reported by Spain. - Mod.MPP]

